def reviews(): return '<section class="reviews"><p class="eyebrow">Reputation</p><h2>What public review snippets emphasize: quality, response, respect.</h2><div class="review-grid"><blockquote>“The work is high quality!”</blockquote><blockquote>“A great choice if you want quality work without hassle.”</blockquote><blockquote>“Jag Electric and the technician Jacob did a wonderful job!”</blockquote><blockquote>“Fair prices and quality work. They actually clean up after themselves and respect your property.”</blockquote><blockquote>“Very courteous. Fast response.”</blockquote></div><a class="btn ghost" href="/reviews">See review sources</a></section>'
def service_page(slug,title,pk,kw,ctx):
 paras=[f'{title} should start with a real conversation about the building, the load, and what the owner is trying to accomplish. JAG Electric is based in Galena and serves Pittsburg and nearby communities, so this page is written for the homes, rentals, shops, and remodels common across southeast Kansas and the Four State area. The goal is not to sell a mystery repair. The goal is to help a homeowner, landlord, builder, or business owner explain the electrical problem clearly enough that the first call is useful.',f'For {kw}, the most important detail is what changed before the issue appeared. Sometimes a breaker trip starts after a new appliance. Sometimes a remodel opens a wall and reveals old wiring. Sometimes a fixture is blamed when the switch, junction, or circuit is the real issue. Public listings describe JAG Electric as a residential and commercial electrical contractor handling panel upgrades, lighting, outlet repairs, remodel wiring, new construction wiring, computer cable installation, switchboards, connectors, and related electrical services.',f'Local electrical work around Galena, Pittsburg, Frontenac, Girard, Joplin, and nearby towns often involves a mix of older homes, newer additions, rental properties, garages, shops, and small commercial spaces. That mix matters because electrical service is rarely only about one device. A {title.lower()} call may touch the panel, grounding, circuit length, fixture box, switch location, access, and future plans for the room. Good preparation helps the electrician understand whether the owner needs a repair, an upgrade, a remodel rough-in, or a phased plan.',f'A strong estimate conversation should include the property address or town, the age of the home if known, whether the work is residential or commercial, what room or system is affected, and whether the problem is urgent or planned. If a breaker is tripping, note what is running when it trips. If lights flicker, note whether it is one fixture, one room, or the whole house. If the project is part of a remodel, note whether walls are open, cabinets are moving, or new equipment is being added.',f'Photos help when they are useful photos. A clear image of the panel, affected fixture, outlet or switch location, room, and any visible labels can save time during scheduling. Representative electrical photos are used to make the service pages feel real while staying honest: these images are not claimed as JAG Electric job photos unless the business confirms them later. Verified facts stay separate from representative visuals: Galena base, phone, email, public reputation signals, and listed services.',f'Homeowners shopping for {kw} near Pittsburg or Galena should know what not to assume. The page should not promise a license number it has not verified, a twenty-four-hour emergency guarantee when public hours conflict, a fake same-day result, or message delivery that has not been wired and tested. JAG Electric’s estimate-prep tool follows that rule: it organizes call notes and gives the visitor a verified phone and email path.',f'For remodels and additions, electrical planning should happen early enough to avoid rework. A kitchen update can change appliance loads, lighting, outlets, dedicated circuits, and panel capacity. A bathroom remodel can involve GFCI protection, lighting, fans, and switches. A garage or shop project can raise questions about equipment, future tools, and safe access. Even when the service need is narrower, the best result comes from looking at the circuit and not just the visible device.',f'Commercial customers need the same clarity in a different language. A small office, retail space, rental unit, or shop may need lighting changes, added outlets, computer cable support, panel review, or electrical work tied to a tenant improvement. Public BBB information for JAG Electric lists commercial and residential electrical contractor services, including new construction and remodels. This page keeps both homeowner and business language present without making unsupported claims about large industrial projects or emergency dispatch.',f'When calling about {title.lower()}, describe the job in plain English: what is happening, where it is happening, what changed, and what outcome you want. If this is a repair, explain the symptom. If this is an upgrade, explain the future use. If this is remodel wiring, explain the timeline and what other trades are doing. If this is commercial work, explain operating hours and access constraints. That gives the electrician a cleaner path to scheduling and a more useful first visit.',f'The bottom line for {kw} near Galena and Pittsburg is simple: electrical work should be scoped with care before it is sold with slogans. This page is intentionally deeper than a thin service card because customers need substance. They need to know JAG Electric handles the category, understands the local service area, and gives them a practical way to start. Use the estimate-prep tool, call {phone}, or email {email} with photos and a short description.']
 other=''.join(f'<a href="/services/{s[0]}">{s[1]}</a>' for s in services if s[0]!=slug)
 body=hero('Electrical service',title,f'Local {kw} for Galena, Pittsburg, and nearby communities — practical planning for {ctx}.')+f'<section class="photo-feature">{photo(pk,title)}<div><h2>{title} work that starts with a real scope conversation.</h2><p>{paras[0]}</p><p>{paras[1]}</p></div></section><section class="long-copy">'+''.join(f'<p>{p}</p>' for p in paras[2:])+'</section>'+f'<section class="faq-grid"><h2>Questions to answer before calling</h2><div><h3>What changed?</h3><p>New appliances, remodel work, storms, tripping breakers, flickering lights, or added equipment can change scope.</p></div><div><h3>What photos help?</h3><p>Panel, fixture, switch, outlet, room, exterior wall, and visible labels.</p></div><div><h3>What towns are in range?</h3><p>JAG Electric is based in Galena and serves Pittsburg and nearby areas. Call to confirm scheduling.</p></div></section><section class="related"><h2>Related electrical services</h2><div class="mini-links">{other}</div></section>'+cta(title.lower())+'</main>'
 return header(f'{title} | JAG Electric',f'{title} near Galena and Pittsburg, KS. JAG Electric helps plan {kw} with clear local electrical service information.',body)
def city_page(slug,name,intro):
 paras=[f'People looking for an electrician in {name} are usually trying to solve a real problem: a breaker keeps tripping, a remodel needs wiring, a porch light stopped working, outlets are loose, a rental needs repair, or a small business needs lighting and power cleaned up before work can continue. JAG Electric is based in Galena, Kansas and serves Pittsburg and nearby areas, so this page is written for local homeowners, landlords, builders, and small-business owners who want the first call to be clear.',intro,f'The most useful way to start an electrical conversation in {name} is to describe the building and the symptom. A house built decades ago may have different panel capacity, wiring access, outlet placement, and fixture boxes than a newer home. A rental property may need repairs that are safe, documented, and scheduled around tenants. A remodel may need work coordinated with cabinets, drywall, HVAC, plumbing, or flooring. A shop or office may need commercial electrical planning without inflated promises. That is why the estimate-prep tool organizes notes instead of pretending to give a fake instant quote.',f'JAG Electric’s public business information supports a practical service mix: residential and commercial electrical contractor work, new construction and remodel wiring, panel upgrades, lighting, outlet repairs, computer cable installation, switchboards, connectors, and related electrical services. The page does not claim an unverified license number, a fake emergency guarantee, or a separate office in {name}. It simply gives local customers enough detail to decide whether to call and what to have ready.',f'For homeowners in {name}, common projects can include fixture installation, kitchen or bathroom electrical changes, breaker issues, exterior lights, outlets that stopped working, GFCI questions, panel conversations, and wiring support during additions or remodels. The important thing is not to self-diagnose past the safe point. If there is heat, burning smell, sparking, or a clearly unsafe condition, stop using the circuit and call. For normal planning, write down what changed, what triggers the problem, and whether photos are available.',f'For landlords and property managers around {name}, electrical communication matters because repairs often involve tenants, access windows, repeat symptoms, and documentation. A clear call summary should include the unit address, room affected, symptom, tenant availability, and whether the issue affects lights, outlets, panel, appliances, or exterior equipment. That helps separate a simple repair from a larger wiring or panel conversation.',f'For builders, remodelers, and small commercial customers near {name}, electrical work should be brought into the project early. The electrician needs to know where walls are open, what equipment is planned, where fixtures and switches belong, how circuits should be staged, and whether the panel can support the new load. Commercial spaces can add access constraints, business hours, tenant rules, and computer or lighting needs.',f'Photos matter because electrical work is physical: panels, wiring, switches, access, labels, and working conditions. Representative electrical images are used to show that context, but they are not described as JAG Electric project photos unless confirmed later. Verified proof stays separate: Google/GBP rating supplied by Toby, Facebook recommendation signal, BBB A+ accreditation listing, and HomeAdvisor information.',f'A useful {name} electrical page should help the visitor, not just repeat city names. That means the page should mention nearby service needs, explain the work categories, link to the service pages, and give a useful next action. It should also be clear that JAG Electric is based in Galena and that service availability should be confirmed by phone.',f'If you are near {name} and need electrical help, start with the estimate-prep page or call {phone}. Be ready with the address or town, whether the property is residential or commercial, what room or system is affected, what changed recently, and whether the work is repair, upgrade, remodel, new construction, or commercial planning. Email photos to {email} if helpful. The goal is a cleaner first conversation and a better-scoped electrical visit.',f'That practical preparation is what makes a local electrician page useful. Instead of asking a visitor to trust a generic claim, the page gives them service links, local context, photo-backed visual confidence, and a clear contact path. For {name}, the next move is simple: gather the details, include safe photos when possible, and contact JAG Electric for scheduling availability.',f'For customers comparing electricians near {name}, the useful signal is not a flashy promise. It is whether the page names the real work, explains the service radius honestly, shows electrical context, and gives a direct phone path. This page is built around the real work categories: panel upgrades, rewiring, fixture work, outlet and switch repair, remodel wiring, commercial electrical planning, and a practical estimate-prep summary. That detail helps customers understand what JAG Electric can help plan in the area.']
 links=''.join(f'<a href="/services/{s[0]}">{s[1]}</a>' for s in services)
 body=hero('Service-area page',f'{name} electrician service planning',f'{intro} JAG Electric serves the region from its Galena base; call to confirm scheduling for your address.')+f'<section class="photo-feature">{photo("profile" if slug=="galena-ks" else "work",name+" electrical service planning")}<div><h2>Electrical help near {name}, written for real local calls.</h2><p>{paras[0]}</p><p>{paras[1]}</p></div></section><section class="long-copy">'+''.join(f'<p>{p}</p>' for p in paras[2:])+'</section>'+f'<section class="service-grid area-services">{links}</section>'+cta(name+' electrical work')+'</main>'
 return header(f'{name} Electrician | JAG Electric',f'JAG Electric service-area page for {name}: panel upgrades, rewiring, lighting, outlets, remodel wiring, and commercial electrical planning.',body)
